org.aavso.tools.vstar.plugin.period
Class PeriodAnalysisPluginBase

java.lang.Object
  org.aavso.tools.vstar.plugin.period.PeriodAnalysisPluginBase
All Implemented Interfaces:
PluginBase
Direct Known Subclasses:
DcDftPeriodAnalysisPlugin
public abstract class PeriodAnalysisPluginBase
extends java.lang.Object
implements PluginBase

This is the abstract base class for all period analysis plugin classes.

Period analysis plugins will appear in VStar's Analysis -> Period Search menu when its jar file is placed into the vstar_plugins directory.

public void sendPeriodChangeMessage(double period)
Send a period change message.

meanSourceSeriesChangeAction

protected abstract void meanSourceSeriesChangeAction(MeanSourceSeriesChangeMessage message)
When the mean source series changes, a plugin may want to discard previous computation results and GUI components, so the plugin will listen for such messages. Of course, a plugin will only care about such messages if the period analysis computations are based upon the current mean series.

Parameters:
The - mean source series change message.
